minianapana_page_title.string: Mini Anapana Meditation - An Introductory Session by Mr. S.N. Goenka
minianapana_page_title.translation: Мини Анапана медитация - въвеждаща сесия на С.Н. Гоенка

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Занимания с Мини Анапана трябва да се извършват в тиха зала или стая подходяща за медитация
  2. Участниците трябва да слушат и практикуват внимателно, седейки с изправен гръб, запазвайки пълно мълчание през цялото занимание
  3. Нито домакина, нито някой друг не трябва да дава каквито и да е други указания, наживо или чрез запис; единствените указания, които се дават, трябва да са от записа Мини Анапана на г-н Гоенка
  4. Не трябва да се събират такси за слушането на Мини Анапана

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: Бележка: Участници, които са практикували занимания с Мини Анапана, не се считат за "Стари ученици" в тази традиция. Те не могат да участват в програми, които са предназначени "Само за стари ученици".

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Meditace mini-ánápána by se měla konat v tiché místnosti vhodné pro meditaci.
  2. Účastníci musí pozorně poslouchat a následovat instrukce, sedět s rovnými zády a udržovat naprosté ticho v průběhu celého sezení.
  3. Organizátor sezení ani nikdo jiný by neměl dávat další instrukce, ať už přímo nebo ve formě jiné nahrávky. Jedinými instrukcemi by měly být pokyny pana Goenky v nahrávce mini-ánápána.
  4. Za účast na meditaci mini-ánápána se nesmí vybírat žádný poplatek.

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: Poznámka: Účastníci meditace mini-ánápána nejsou bráni jako “staří studenti” této tradice. Nemohou se tedy účastnit žádného z kurzů označených “pouze pro staré studenty”.

  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session

minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Eine Mini-Anapana-Meditationssitzung sollte in einer ruhigen Halle oder einem für die Meditation geeigenten Raum stattfinden.
  2. Die Teilnehmer müssen sorgfältig zuhören und praktizieren. Sie sollten dabei aufrecht sitzen und während der gesamten Sitzung das Schweigen einhalten.
  3. Weder die Person, die die Sitzung leitet, noch irgendjemand anderes sollte irgendwelche weiteren Anweisungen geben. Die einzigen Anweisungen sollten die von Goenkajis Mini-Anapana-Aufnahme sein.
  4. Die Teilnahme an einer Mini-Anapana-Meditation sollte immer unentgeltlich sein.

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Μία μικρή συνεδρία Anapana πρέπει να γίνεται σε σιωπηλή αίθουσα ή δωμάτιο κατάλληλο για διαλογισμό
  2. ΟΙ συμμετέχοντες πρέπει να ακούν και να ασκούνται προσεκτικά, να κάθονται με την πλάτη τους ίσια ενώ θα πρέπει να διατηρούν απόλυτη ησυχία καθόλη τη διάρκεια της συνεδρίας
  3. Ούτε το άτομο που φιλοξενεί τη συνεδρία ούτε οποιοσδήποτε άλλος πρέπει να δίνει άλλες οδηγίες, ζωντανά ή ηχογραφημένες. Οι μόνες οδηγίες που πρέπει να δίνονται είναι οι ηχογραφήσεις του κου Goenka σχετικά με τη μικρή Anapana
  4. Δεν πρέπει να υπάρχει η οποιαδήποτε χρέωση για συμμετοχή σε μία μικρή συνεδρία Anapana

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".

minianapana_page_title.string: Mini Anapana Meditation - An Introductory Session by Mr. S.N. Goenka
minianapana_page_title.translation: Mini Anapana - Una sesión de introducción a la Meditación Anapana por S.N. Goenka

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Ésta debe reproducirse en una sala silenciosa o en un cuarto apto para meditar
  2. Se solicita que los practicantes lo escuchen con una actitud respetuosa, sentados con una postura erguida y mantener silencio absoluto durante toda la sesión
  3. Nadie debe dar ninguna otra instrucción, ya sea en vivo o por medio de alguna otra reproducción de audio. Las únicas instrucciones deben ser las de la grabación de Mini Anapana por Goenkaji
  4. No deberá solicitarse cargo alguno por asistir a la sesión de “Mini Anapana”

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: Nota: Aquellas personas que aprendan Anapana en la sesión corta de Mini Anapana no se serán consideradas como “Estudiantes Antiguos” en esta tradición, por lo que no pueden participar en programas designados para "Estudiantes Antiguos" solamente.

minianapana_guidelines.string:

  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session

1. جلسه مینی آناپانا باید درسالن یا اتاق مناسب مراقبه در سکوت برگذار شود.
  2. شرکت کنندگان باید به دقت گوش نموده و در وضعیت نشسته با پشتی صاف و حفظ سکوت کامل در طول کل جلسه به تمرین بپردازند.
  3. نه کسی که میزبان جلسه است و نه هیچ کس دیگری نباید هیچ دستورالعمل دیگری به شکل شفاهی یا ضبط شده ارایه دهد. دستورالعمل های مینی آناپانا فقط صدای ضبط شده آقای گوینکا می باشد .
  4. نه کسی که میزبان جلسه است و نه هیچ کس دیگری نباید هیچ دستورالعمل دیگری به شکل شفاهی یا ضبط شده ارایه دهد. دستورالعمل های مینی آناپانا فقط صدای ضبط شده آقای گوینکا می باشد .

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".

minianapana_page_title.string: Mini Anapana Meditation - An Introductory Session by Mr. S.N. Goenka
minianapana_page_title.translation: Mini-anapanameditaatio - S.N. Goenkan pitämä meditaation esittely

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Mini-anapanameditaatio tulee järjestää vain hiljaisessa salissa tai huoneessa, joka on sopiva meditointiin.
  2. Osallistujien on kuunneltava ohjeita ja toimittava tarkasti niiden mukaan. Heidän on istuttava selkä suorassa ja pysyttävä hiljaa koko meditaation ajan.
  3. Tilaisuuden isännän tai kenenkään muun ei tule antaa mitään muita ohjeita, ei paikan päällä puhuttuna eikä nauhalta. Ainoat ohjeet, jotka kuullaan, ovat Goenkajin mini-anapanan ohjeet nauhalta.
  4. Mini-anapanameditaatioon osallistumisesta ei saa periä maksua.

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: Huom: Mini-anapanameditaatioon osallistuneet eivät ole tämän perinteen niin kutsuttuja "vanhoja oppilaita", eivätkä he voi osallistua vain vanhoille oppilaille tarkoitettuihin aktiviteetteihin.

1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Une session de Mini Anapana doit être proposée dans un hall tranquille ou une pièce appropriée à la méditation
  2. Les participants doivent écouter et pratiquer attentivement, assis le dos droit et en maintenant un silence complet pendant la totalité de la session
  3. Ni la personne qui accueille la session, ni toute autre personne ne doit donner d'autres instructions, en direct ou enregistrées ; les seules instructions doivent être celles de l'enregistrement de Mini Anapana de M. Goenka
  4. Aucun frais d'aucune sorte ne doit être demandé pour la participation à une session de Mini Anapana

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: Note: Les participants qui participent à des sessions de Mini Anapana ne seront pas considérés comme des "anciens étudiants" dans cette tradition. Ils ne peuvent participer à aucun programme désigné comme étant "uniquement pour les anciens étudiants".

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. छोटा आनापान सत्र एक शांत हॉल या ध्यान के लिए उपयुक्त कक्ष में आयोजित किया जाना चाहिए
  2. प्रतिभागियों को पूरे सत्र के दौरान पीठ सीधी रखकर बैठकर पुरी शांतता रखकर सुनिये और सावधानीसे अभ्यास करना चाहिए
  3. सत्रको मेजबानी करनेवाली व्यक्ति या किसी अन्य व्यक्तीको कोइभी निर्देश, सजीव अथवा रेकॉर्डेड देना नही चाहिए; निर्देश केवल श्री गोयनका के छोटे आनापान रिकॉर्डिंग की ही होना चाहिए
  4. एक छोटे आनापान सत्र में भाग लेने के लिए कोई भी शुल्क नहीं होना चाहिए

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: टिप:छोटे आनापान सत्र में भाग लेने वाले प्रतिभागियों को इस परंपरा में 'पुराना छात्र "के रूप में नहीं माना जाएगा, "केवल पुराने छात्रों के लिए" के रूप में नामित किसी भी कार्यक्रम में भाग नहीं ले सकते।

  4. A Mini Anapana tréningnek ingyenesnek kell lennie.

minianapana_guidelines_section_title.translation: មគ្គទេសក៍​ណែនាំ

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. ការបដិបត្តិ​អានាបាណស្សតិ​បឋម គួរ​ធ្វើ​ឡើង​នៅក្នុង​សាល ឬ បន្ទប់​ស្ងប់ស្ងាត់ ដែល​សមស្រប​សម្រាប់​ការចម្រើន​កម្មដ្ឋាន
  2. អ្នកចូលរួម​ត្រូវតែ​ស្ដាប់​ការណែនាំ ហើយ​បដិបត្តិ​ដោយ​យកចិត្ត​ទុកដាក់។ អ្នកបដិបត្តិ​ត្រូវ​អង្គុយ​បញ្ឈរ​ខ្នង​ឲ្យ​ត្រង់ ហើយ​ត្រូវ​រក្សា​អរិយស្ងាត់​ទាំងស្រុង​ក្នុង​អំឡុងពេល​បដិបត្តិ​ទាំងមូល
  3. ទោះ​បុគ្គល​ដែល​ជា​អ្នករៀបចំ ឬក៏​នរណា​ម្នាក់​ផ្សេងទៀត​ក៏​ដោយ មិន​ត្រូវ​ផ្ដល់​សេចក្ដីណែនាំ​អ្វី​ផ្សេងទៀត​ឡើយ ទោះ​ជា​ដោយ​ផ្ទាល់ ឬក៏​តាម​ការថត​ទុក​ក្ដី ពោល​គឺ​មាន​តែ​សេចក្ដីណែនាំ​ដែល​បាន​ថត​ទុក​របស់​លោក ស.ន. ហ្គោឥនកា ប៉ុណ្ណោះ ដែល​អាច​ផ្ដល់​ជូន​បាន។
  4. គ្មាន​ការគិត​ប្រាក់​អ្វី​ទាំងអស់​ចំពោះ​ការចូលរួម​បដិបត្តិ​អានាបាណស្សតិ​បឋម​នេះ

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: សម្គាល់៖ អ្នកចូលរួម​បដិបត្តិ​អានាបាណស្សតិ​បឋម​នេះ​នឹង​មិន​ត្រូវ​បាន​ចាត់ទុក​ថា​ជា "សិស្សចាស់" នៅក្នុង​ប្រពៃណី​នេះ​ឡើយ។ ពួកគេ​មិន​អាច​ចូលរួម​នៅក្នុង​កម្មវិធី​ផ្សេងទៀត​ដែល​បាន​កំណត់​ថា "សម្រាប់​សិស្សចាស់​ប៉ុណ្ណោះ" ឡើយ។

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. लहान आनापान सत्र एक शांत हॉल किंवा ध्यानायोग्य खोलीत आयोजित करावीत
  2. सहभागीदारानी पूर्ण सत्रादरम्यान पाठ ताठ ठेवून बसून पूर्ण शांतता राखत ऐकावे आणि सावधपणे अभ्यास करावा
  3. सत्र आयोजन करणारी यजमान व्यक्ती किंवा इतर कोणतीही अन्य व्यक्ती ह्यांनी कोणत्याही सूचना, सजीव किंवा रेकॉर्डेड देऊ नयेत; फक्त श्री गोएंका च्या छोट्या आनापान रेकॉर्डिंग मधीलच सूचना असाव्यात
  4. आनापानच्या छोट्या सत्रामध्ये भाग घेणाऱ्यांसाठी कोणतेही शुल्क नसावे

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: टिप:छोटे आनापान सत्रामध्ये भाग घेणाऱ्यांना ह्या परंपरेमध्ये "जुने विद्यार्थी" म्हणून मानले जाणार नाही."फक्त जुन्या विद्यार्थ्यांठी" म्हणून नियुक्त केलेल्या कोणताही कार्यक्रमामध्ये त्यांना सहभागी होता येणार नाही.

minianapana_page_title.string: Mini Anapana Meditation - An Introductory Session by Mr. S.N. Goenka
minianapana_page_title.translation: Mini meditação Anapana – Uma Sessão Introdutória por S. N. Goenka.

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Uma sessão de mini Anapana deve ser conduzida em uma sala tranquila ou em uma sala apropriada para meditação
  2. Os participantes devem escutar e praticar cuidadosamente, sentando-se com suas costas eretas, enquanto mantêm completo silêncio durante toda a duração da sessão
  3. Nem a pessoa que abriga a sessão nem qualquer outra pessoa deve dar qualquer outra instrução, ao vivo ou gravada. A única instrução dada deve se a gravação da mini Anapana de S. N. Goenka
  4. Não deve haver qualquer cobrança de taxas para frequentar uma sessão de mini Anapana

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: Nota: Os participantes que frequentarem as sessões de mini Anapana não serão considerados “alunos antigos” nesta tradição. Não podem participar de nenhum programa designado para “somente para alunos antigos”.

minianapana_guidelines.translation:
• කුඩා ආනාපාන සැසියක් පැවැත්විය හැකි වන්නේ භාවනාවට සුදුසු නිහඬ ශාලාවක හෝ කාමරයක ය
  • මෙයට සහභාගි වන්නන් පිටකෙළින් තබා ගෙන සැසිය අවසන් වනතෙක්ම සම්පූර්ණ නිශ්ශබ්දතාවය රකි‍මින් හොඳින් ඇහුම්කන් දෙමින් භාවනාවේ යෙදිය යුතුයි

minianapana_page_title.translation: లఘు ఆనాపాన కార్యక్రమం - శ్రీ గోయెంక గారిచే ఒక పరిచయ కార్యక్రమం

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. ధ్యానంకు అనువైన హాల్ లేదా గదులలో మాత్రమే లఘు ఆనాపాన ధ్యాన కార్యక్రమంను నిర్వహించాలి
  2. ఈ ధ్యాన కార్యక్రమంలో పాల్గొనే వారందరూ ఆర్య మౌనమును పాటిస్తూ, వెన్నుముకను నేరుగా ఉంచి కూర్చొని, సూచనలను జాగ్రతగా వింటూ సాధన చేయాలి.
  3. ఈ కార్యక్రమం నిర్వహించే వ్యక్తి లేక మరెవరైనా కూడా నేరుగా లేదా రికార్డు చేసిన వేరే ఏ సూచనలను ఇవ్వరాదు. శ్రీ గోయెంక గారు ఇచ్చిన లఘు ఆనాపాన సూచనల రికార్డింగ్ మాత్రమే ఉపయోగించాలి.
  4. ఈ లఘు ఆనాపాన కార్యక్రమానికి ఎటువంటి రుసుము ఉండకూడదు.

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: గమనిక: లఘు ఆనాపాన కార్యక్రమంలో పాల్గొనే వాళ్ళు ఈ సాంప్రదాయంలో "పాత సాధకులు" గా పరిగణింపబడరు. "పాత సాధకులకు" మాత్రమే రూపొందించబడిన మరే కార్యక్రమాలలోనూ వారు పాల్గొన లేరు.

minianapana_page_title.translation: การปฏิบัติอานาปานสติแบบย่อ - การปฏิบัติเบื้องต้น โดยท่านอาจารย์โกเอ็นก้า

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. การปฏิบัติอานาปานสติแบบย่อนี้ ควรปฏิบัติในห้องที่เงียบสงบ เหมาะแก่การปฏิบัติภาวนา
  2. ผู้ปฏิบัติควรฟังและปฏิบัติอย่างจริงจัง ควรนั่งหลังตรงและตั้งใจรักษาความเงียบอย่างเคร่งครัด ตลอดการฝึกอบรม
  3. ไม่อนุญาตให้ผู้ใดทำการสอนใดๆทั้งสิ้น คำสอนจะมาจากเทปบันทึกภาพและเสียงของท่านอาจารย์โกเอ็นก้าเท่านั้น
  4. ไม่มีการเรียกเก็บค่าใช้จ่ายใดๆ ในการเข้าปฏิบัติอานาปานสติช่วงสั้นๆ นี้

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: หมายเหตุ: ผู้ที่ได้ผ่านการอบรมอานาปานสติแบบย่อนี้ ยังไม่นับเป็น”ผู้ปฏิบัติเก่าในแนวทางนี้" จึงไม่สามารถเข้าร่วมการอบรมในหลักสูตรที่กำหนดไว้เฉพาะ ”สำหรับผู้ปฏิบัติเก่าเท่านั้น”

minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. Phiên thực hành thiền Anapana giản lược cần được tổ chức trong một thiền đường nhỏ hoặc phòng phù hợp cho việc thực hành thiền
  2. Những người tham gia phải nghe và làm theo hướng dẫn một cách thận trọng, giữ lưng thẳng và duy trì sự im lặng trong suốt phiên thực hành
  3. Không một ai, kể cả người đứng ra tổ chức phiên thực hành, được phép đưa ra bất kỳ hướng dẫn nào khác, dù là hướng dẫn trực tiếp hay qua băng thu hình/tiếng. Băng ghi hình/tiếng Hướng dẫn Thiền Anapana (thiền hơi thở) của thiền sư Goenka là nội dung hướng dẫn duy nhất.
  4. Không được phép thu phí đối với những người tham dự dưới bất kỳ hình thức nào

minianapana_page_title.translation: 迷你觀息法 - 介紹及練習 - SN葛印卡先生

minianapana_guidelines.string:
1. A Mini Anapana session should be conducted in a quiet hall or room suitable for meditation
  2. Participants must listen and practice carefully, sitting with their backs straight while maintaining complete silence through out the entire session
  3. Neither the person hosting the session nor anyone else should give any other instructions, live or recorded; the only instructions given should be that of Mr. Goenka's Mini Anapana recording
  4. There should be no charge whatsoever for attending a Mini Anapana session
minianapana_guidelines.translation:
1. 迷你觀息法静坐練習應在適於静坐的安靜大廳或房間进行。
  2. 整個過程，參加者必須傾聽，仔細練習，背部挺直的坐著，同時保持完全的靜默。
  3. 任何人包括主持人都不應給於任何其它指導，無論是现場或錄音方式。唯一的指導應是葛印卡老師的迷你觀息法錄音。
  4. 不可向出席迷你觀息法練習者收取任何費用。

minianapana_guidelines_note.string: Note: Participants who attend Mini Anapana sessions will not be considered as "Old Students" in this tradition. They can not participate in any programs designated as "For Old Students only".
minianapana_guidelines_note.translation: 附住： 參加學習過迷你觀息法的人不算｢此傳承的舊生｣。他們不能參加任何註明｢限舊生｣參加的活動。
